{
  "stem": "25651.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh no, I've got much earlier memories than that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went to Poland quite often, because my father was imported-- importing rabbit skin furs for the industry in my hometown, which was the manufacturer of felt hats, and felt is made up of the pile of rabbit skins.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in the 25 years that we lived in Novy Jicin, my father more or less supplied all the three factories with rabbit skin.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we-- we traveled to Poland quite often in prewar years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think I've been there about three or four times as a child.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One particular vivid memory is around 1933, perhaps 1934.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's really quite early in my life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember that both my brother, [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Milos, ?] and I were bought new blue overcoats and black Wellingtons-- shiny, new black Wellingtons-- because we went, actually, in the winter to a town called Zakopane in the mountains, and we spent the week in Zakopane.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father was buying rabbit skins on the telephone.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The situation-- when I asked my father about this early memory after the war, I said, why were you on the telephone all the time?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- or why didn't you go to Warsaw and to the various places where rabbit skins were being sold?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So he said, well, actually, I wasn't telling people that I was in Poland because as soon as I came to Poland, the price rose.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what's a memory that you have of your mother at an early age?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That particular time was important, and I'm not sure whether it was the visit in 1933 or the visit in 1934.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "During the time that we were in Krakow with my aunt and my uncle-- that was my father's youngest sister, [?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Pepcha. ?] My uncle's name was Lvov Besen.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
